26/01/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament held its first session of the year on Wednesday (25 January). A total of 68 new drafts must be debated and passed within the session, set to continue until mid-February. The list includes draft agreements on settling Croatia's debts to Italy and the Paris Club.
In other news, the Croatian and Hungarian governments hold a joint session Thursday in Budapest. The focus is bilateral co-operation, cross-border projects, and the countries' joint candidacy for hosting the 2012 European Football Championship. (HRT - 26/01/06; HINA - 25/01/06)
